# Deployment

This app deploys with [Kamal](https://kamal-deploy.org/) â€” Docker-based, zero-downtime deploys to any VPS.

## Prerequisites

- Docker installed locally
- A server (Ubuntu 22.04+ recommended) with Docker and SSH access
- A container registry account (GitHub Container Registry is configured by default)
- A domain name pointed at your server's IP

## First-time setup

### 1. Configure your server and domain

Edit `config/deploy.yml`:

```yaml
servers:
  web:
    - 1.2.3.4              # your server IP

# proxy:                   # uncomment to enable SSL
#   ssl: true
#   host: my-app.example.com  # your domain
```

### 2. Set secrets

Copy `.kamal/secrets.tmpl` â†’ `.kamal/secrets` and fill in values:

```bash
cp .kamal/secrets.tmpl .kamal/secrets
# edit .kamal/secrets with your real values
```

```
KAMAL_REGISTRY_PASSWORD=ghp_yourGitHubToken
RAILS_MASTER_KEY=yourMasterKey
```

Get your `RAILS_MASTER_KEY` from `config/master.key` (generated by Rails, never committed).

### 3. Bootstrap the server

```bash
bundle exec kamal setup
```

This installs Docker on the server, configures the proxy, and runs your first deploy.

### 4. Subsequent deploys

```bash
bundle exec kamal deploy
# or
make deploy
```

## CI/CD (automatic deploys)

The `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` workflow deploys automatically on every push to `main`.

Required GitHub repository secrets:

| Secret | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `DEPLOY_KEY` | SSH private key with access to your server |
| `KAMAL_REGISTRY_PASSWORD` | GitHub token with `write:packages` scope |
| `RAILS_MASTER_KEY` | From `config/master.key` |

## Environment variables

| Variable | Required | Default | Description |
|----------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `RAILS_MASTER_KEY` | Yes | â€” | Decrypts `config/credentials.yml.enc` |
| `DATABASE_ADAPTER` | No | `sqlite3` | `sqlite3` or `mysql2` |
| `DB_USERNAME` | If MySQL | `root` | Database username |
| `DB_PASSWORD` | If MySQL | â€” | Database password |
| `DB_HOST` | If MySQL | `localhost` | Database host |
| `MAILER_FROM_ADDRESS` | No | `noreply@example.com` | Sender email |
| `SMTP_ADDRESS` | No | â€” | SMTP server host |
| `SMTP_PORT` | No | `587` | SMTP port |
| `SMTP_USERNAME` | No | â€” | SMTP username |
| `SMTP_PASSWORD` | No | â€” | SMTP password |
| `BASE_URL` | No | `localhost` | Public URL for mailer links |
| `WEB_CONCURRENCY` | No | `2` | Puma worker count |
| `RAILS_MAX_THREADS` | No | `3` | Threads per Puma worker |
| `JOB_CONCURRENCY` | No | `1` | Solid Queue process count |

## Useful Kamal commands

```bash
kamal app logs          # tail production logs
kamal app exec bash     # shell into the running container
kamal app exec "bin/rails console"  # production Rails console
kamal deploy            # deploy latest main
kamal rollback          # roll back to previous version
kamal app restart       # restart app containers
```

## Health check

Kamal monitors `GET /up` â€” the app returns `200 OK` when ready.
If the health check fails after deploy, Kamal automatically rolls back.
